Prague public transport will drive on chip for the first time on Wednesday
Wednesday, October 1, 2008 will be recorded in the history of the Prague Transport Company as the date when the first passengers will board the subway, trams and buses, who will have an electronic coupon in their pocket instead of a paper ticket.
At the moment, he can buy about a hundred thousand people who own an Opencard chip card.
Passengers can buy a 30-day, 90-day and annual coupon (which will be valid from January 1, 2009) and at the same time have it uploaded to their chip card in the information centers and workplaces of the Transport Company at the metro stations Muzeum, M<0xC5><0xAF>stek, Nádra<0xC5><0xBE>í Hole<0xC5><0xA1>ovice, And<0xC4><0x9B>l, Roztyly, Let<0xC5><0x88>any, Kobylisy, Rajská<0xC5><0x99> Garden, Ka<0xC4><0x8D>rov and Lu<0xC4><0x8D>.
Coupons can also be purchased online from yesterday on the website of the Transport Company www.dpp.cz.
More than 400 customers took advantage of the service in the afternoon.
Those who start using the online store can definitely forget about the dispensing windows in the subway stations, where until now they had to regularly stand in long queues for paper tickets.
They buy the coupon online and upload it to their Opencard card in one of the thirteen branches of the City Library.
"At these places, a counter with trained staff is available to passengers, which will help interested parties with online purchases and also upload the purchased coupon to their card," said Martin Opatrn<0xC3><0xBD>, a spokesman for the project.
In addition to libraries, it will also be possible to upload electronic coupons to Opencard in self-service vending machines, which are mounted in several subway vestibules.
What do these machines look like?
They are red, reminiscent of ticket markers, and passengers may have already noticed them at Roztyly, Bud<0xC4><0x9B>jovická, I. P. Pavlova, Florenc and Vltavská metro stations.
"There are five of them in the city now, but by the end of the year there should be eighty," he added.
The coupon checks the driver's place vending machine
The operation of the machines that will start working tomorrow is simple.
Just insert an Opencard chip card into them and the previously paid coupon will be uploaded to it itself.
Electronic coupons are valid from tomorrow not only in the capital, but also in its surroundings.
