The Ministry of the Interior requires that a driver with three administrative penalties for driving under the influence of alcohol must install a system in his car that prevents him from starting the car drunk or if he does not breathe.
The proposal came to light in June this year and is now included in the annual report of the Supreme Prosecutor’s Office, according to which it is a pilot project that will last for one year.
Its goal is to return the driver behind the wheel, therefore, drivers will also have to take a course of traffic re-education.
