According to statistics, between 30 and 75% of motorists charged with drunk driving more than once get back behind the wheel in this state.
Alcolock should prevent this, as it is a system connected to the vehicle that measures the level of alcohol in the exhaled air and prevents the car from starting if the driver does not breathe first or if the alcohol level is higher than the allowed concentration.
Its price exceeds 1,000 euros and would have to be paid by the culprit himself.
A study conducted in the US in 2007 showed that vehicles equipped with this device had a 65% reduction in offences during the first year since its introduction.
In Spain, it is estimated that 115 lives could be saved each year.
The measure is limited to administrative sanctions for two reasons: to deal with this behaviour before it results in a criminal offence.
And in order to facilitate its introduction, since legislation can be implemented in the usual way, however, the necessary adjustment of criminal provisions requires a change in the law.
The device is not yet available in any sales version on the Spanish market, although it has already been tested in some industrial vehicles and public service vehicles.
