Open Office, here we have the third edition of the "anti-Microsoft" package
It’s the release day of Open Office.org 3.0, an open source personal production package that aims to penetrate more and more users, from home to office, from experts to public administration, as a free alternative to the more familiar Microsoft Office.
After about a year of volunteer work, controlled by SUN Microsystem, the new Open Office appears to the general public with various novelties: to the welcome screen and to the revised and improved opening window will be added another, much more essential, as compatibility for the operating system Apple Mac OS X and support for the new version of the ODF format (Open ISO Standart 1.2).
Emphasis is also placed on collaboration with Office 2007, Open Office is able to open a document with a new Microsoft extension (.docx, .xlsx, .pptx).
Interesting are the special features of some models, such as what allows you to reduce the size of a PowerPoint presentation, useful for example for electronic transmission, or the ability to transfer a PDF folder to a graphics model and preserve the original appearance of the page.
Still from this point of view, we can create "PDF hybrid" documents that resemble typical Adobe graphics and have the characteristics of a spreadsheet or text program.
Collaboration is an element that has received many improvements within application programs: in Excel, it is possible to work together between different users and avoid conflicts on changes, in the text program each co-worker is assigned one color for comments to be more clearly identified in the revision phase.
Some companies are also working to transfer some of the features of Open Office to the Web (on the cloud), and should reimagine the final result in the coming weeks.
The Italian version can be downloaded at http://it.openoffice.org/download/3.0.0/download300.html, has been added to the English version, which has been on the mirror since Friday.
In addition to Windows and Mac OS, as usual, the package is also available for the Linux operating system.
Also, the installation CD can be sent home or to the workplace on request.
And if the topic of freeware can be a drag to expand in homes, it is on the Open Office business area that the package bets a lot, and can already count on a variety of projects implemented in public administration and schools.
And there is no shortage of training, consulting and assistance services ideal for small and medium-sized businesses, which could open up business prospects.
Open Office consists of five main models: Writer, for video typing replacing Word; Calc is a spreadsheet that aims to replace Excel; Impress for PowerPoint-like presentations; Dbase, as in the case of the more famous Access, is a program that allows you to work on databases; Draw, after all, is a graphical model.
The goal for 2008 is to reach 5 million downloads, and if we consider that to date we are at almost 3 million and 600 thousand, with the release of a new version it is possible that this predicted number can even be exceeded.
