Students victims of expensive rents - up to 900 euros per room
The rental market for university students does not know the crisis.
According to the latest research by Sunia, a tenant union, renting a single room can cost a student up to 900 euros in Milan, 700 in Florence, 650 in Naples, 600 in Rome.
“The phenomenon has already reached such proportions that entire strata of students have lost the right to study because of the overall too high prices that their families would have to bear,” explains Laura Mariani, head of Sunia’s studios, “the high demand from students in this city has distorted the market in such a way that it has spurred a process of price increases that has spread even to residents.”
In most cases, lease offers contain several offences: contracts freely, unregistered, without a limited lease, associated sub-lease.
For Sunja, an exceptional intervention is needed, which could regulate prices thanks to the revision of taxes.
